<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About McKenzie Lake</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Development of McKenzie Lake real estate began in 1982 with an artificial lake added on the lines of the Bonavista man-made lake. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Named after one of the earliest settlers, J. McKenzie, the community became part of Calgary in 1970. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Situated on the western banks of Bow River in the southeast quadrant of Calgary, Alberta, McKenzie Lake is a residential community that features luxury estate homes. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">To the north of McKenzie Lake community is d130 Avenue SE, while the Deerfoot Trail runs along the eastern border. The southern border of this community is marked by Stoney Trail.</p>
        </div>
